# Analysis of Main Target Image

## Count & Layers
The structure consists of 7 building blocks arranged in 4 layers:
- Bottom layer: 1 yellow cube
- Second layer: 1 red block with a semi-circular cutout
- Third layer: 1 green horizontal rectangular block
- Top layer: 2 blue cubes side by side
- Side components: 2 orange triangular/wedge-shaped blocks attached to the right side

## Spatial Relationships
- The yellow cube forms the base at the bottom
- The red block with cutout sits directly on top of the yellow cube
- The green rectangular block is positioned horizontally on top of the red block
- The two blue cubes sit side by side on top of the green block
- One orange triangular block is positioned on the right side at the middle height
- Another orange triangular block appears to be behind or beside the first orange block

# Required Blocks from Dictionary

Based on the analysis, I need the following blocks:
- Block #4: Yellow cube (for the base)
- Block #1: Red block with semi-circular cutout
- Block #6: Green horizontal rectangular block
- Block #2: Blue cube (needed twice)
- Block #15: Orange triangular block (right-facing wedge)
- Block #14: Orange triangular block (angled differently than #15)

# Assembly Order

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 4
    Step2: Move block with index 1
    Step3: Move block with index 6
    Step4: Move block with index 15
    Step5: Move block with index 14
    Step6: Move block with index 2
    Step7: Move block with index 2
}
```

This assembly sequence builds from the bottom up, starting with the foundation and working toward the top, with the side components added before the top layer to ensure proper structural integrity.
